-- Tanox shareholders approve merger with Genentech
-- 
-- Mon Jan 15, 2007 2:59pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/15/businesspro-tanox-genentech-dc-idUSWEN217020070115

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shareholders of biotechnology company 
Tanox Inc. TNOX.O voted to approve the company's $919 million 
merger agreement with Genentech Inc. DNA.N, Tanox said on 
Monday. 

  About 34 million Tanox shares were voted in favor of the 
merger, representing more than three-quarters of Tanox's total 
outstanding shares, the company said.  Under the terms of the merger, Tanox shareholders will 
receive $20 cash for each share of common stock held.  The transaction is expected to close during the first 
quarter of 2007.